com.ibm.team.repository.common

Interface IVirtualType.IRegistry

  • Enclosing interface:
    IVirtualType

    public static interface IVirtualType.IRegistry
    Static registry used to locate virtual types.

    Example usage: 

                  public interface ISomeClass extends ISomeClassHandle {
              public static final IVirtualType TYPE = IVirtualType.IRegistry.INSTANCE
                    .getVirtualType(SomePackage.eINSTANCE.getSomeClass().getName(),
                            SomePackage.eNS_URI);

    • Method Detail

      • getVirtualType

        IVirtualType getVirtualType(java.lang.String name,
                          java.lang.String namespace)
        Locates an virtual type given its name and its namespace.
        Parameters:
        name - The virtual type's name; must not be null
        namespace - the virtual type's namespace; must not be null
        Returns:
        the located virtual type or null if the virtual type name and namespace pair was not located in the virtual type registry

      • getAllVirtualTypes

        IVirtualType[] getAllVirtualTypes()
        Locates all virtual types. Abstract types will be excluded.
        Returns:
        all virtual types; never null

      • getAllVirtualTypes

        IVirtualType[] getAllVirtualTypes(boolean includeAbstractTypes)
        Locates all virtual types.
        Parameters:
        includeAbstractTypes - indicates whether abstract types should be included in the returned collection
        Returns:
        all virtual types; never null
